# Backend Architecture

Stack: FastAPI, SQLAlchemy, PostgreSQL, Qdrant.

Pattern: **Service + Repository** (similar to NestJS/Express with an isolated data layer).

## Folder structure

```
backend/
├── app/
│   ├── main.py                 # FastAPI app, middleware, router registration
│   │
│   ├── core/                   # Infrastructure (no business rules)
│   │   ├── config.py
│   │   ├── database.py         # engine, SessionLocal, get_db
│   │   ├── qdrant.py           # Qdrant client
│   │   └── llm/                # LLM adapters (chat/completion)
│   │       ├── base.py         # common protocol/interface
│   │       ├── openai.py
│   │       ├── anthropic.py
│   │       └── factory.py      # get_llm_provider() via config
│   │
│   ├── api/                    # HTTP — feature folders + central router
│   │   └── v1/
│   │       ├── router.py       # aggregates routers from each feature
│   │       ├── health/
│   │       │   └── routes.py
│   │       └── chat/
│   │           ├── routes.py
│   │           └── schemas.py  # DTOs colocated with the feature
│   │
│   ├── models/                 # SQLAlchemy ORM (table definitions only)
│   ├── repositories/           # Data access (Postgres, Qdrant)
│   ├── services/               # Business logic; instantiates repos in __init__
│   ├── agents/                 # Agent orchestration, prompts, and tools
│   └── rag/
│       ├── embeddings/         # embedding adapters (OpenAI, etc.)
│       ├── ingest.py
│       └── retriever.py
│
├── alembic/
├── tests/
├── requirements.txt
└── Dockerfile
```

## Layer responsibilities

| Layer | Responsibility | Depends on |
|-------|----------------|------------|
| `api/v1/router.py` | Aggregates routers from each feature; mounted in `main.py` with prefix `/api/v1` | feature `routes.py` |
| `api/v1/<feature>/` | Feature routes + schemas | `services` |
| `models/` | ORM table/relationship definitions | `core/database` |
| `repositories/` | Queries and persistence (Postgres, Qdrant) | `models`, `core/` |
| `services/` | Business rules, transactions, orchestration | `repositories`, `agents`, `rag` |
| `agents/` | Prompts, tool calling, agent loop | `core/llm`, `repositories`, `rag` |
| `rag/` | Ingestion, retrieval, and vector search | `rag/embeddings`, `repositories` |
| `core/llm/` | LLM adapters (OpenAI, Anthropic, Ollama…) | env vars |
| `rag/embeddings/` | Embedding adapters (may use a different vendor than the LLM) | env vars |
| `core/` | Config, DB, Qdrant | env vars |

## Request flow

```
Client → api/ (route + DTO) → services/ → repositories/ → PostgreSQL / Qdrant
                                ↘ agents/ → core/llm/ (chat)
                                         ↘ rag/ → embeddings/ + Qdrant
```

## LLM providers

Vendor adapters live in `core/llm/` (chat) and `rag/embeddings/` (vectors).
They implement a common interface — no prompts, tool calling, or business rules.

| Type | Location |
|------|----------|
| LLM chat | `core/llm/` |
| Embeddings | `rag/embeddings/` |

`get_db` lives in `core/database.py`. Services instantiate repos — routes only pass the session.

## Design rules

1. Thin routes — no business logic in `api/`
2. Each feature in its own folder — `api/v1/<feature>/routes.py` + `schemas.py`
3. `api/v1/router.py` centralizes and registers all features
4. Services instantiate repos in `__init__` — repos concentrate data access
5. Services must not run queries directly — always via `repositories/`
6. Transactions in `services/` — commit/rollback do not belong in routes
7. `models/` only defines ORM schema; queries live in repos
8. Versioned routes — prefix `/api/v1/` via central router

## Where to put new code

- New HTTP feature → `api/v1/<feature>/routes.py` + register in `api/v1/router.py`
- Feature DTOs → `api/v1/<feature>/schemas.py`
- DB table → `models/<entity>.py`
- Query/persistence → `repositories/<entity>_repository.py`
- Business rule → `services/<domain>_service.py`
- LLM adapter (chat) → `core/llm/<vendor>.py`
- Embedding adapter → `rag/embeddings/<vendor>.py`
- Agent tool → `agents/tools/`
- Ingestion/retrieval → `rag/`

## Legacy (flat) code migration

| Current | Target |
|---------|--------|
| `app/config.py` | `app/core/config.py` |
| `app/database.py` | `app/core/database.py` |
| `app/qdrant.py` | `app/core/qdrant.py` |
| routes in `main.py` | `app/api/v1/<feature>/routes.py` + `app/api/v1/router.py` |
| `main.py` | bootstrap + `app.include_router(v1_router, prefix="/api/v1")` |
